 in vending maching mode (actually, in Gnosis' case, he likely WAS rudely ignoring me - the cheeky bugger)<br><br>Ex. <br><br>/who all Ledenyetz Troupe <br>Players in Everquest<br>-------------------------------<br>Lexxi &lt;Ledenyetz Troupe&gt;<br>Argo &lt;Ledenyetz Troupe&gt; LFG<br>Gnosis &lt;Ledenyetz Troupe&gt; Vendor<br>Uinin &lt;Ledenyetz Troupe&gt;<br><br>and so on...<br><br>2.  How about extending the SEARCH (not buy) function worldwide - or at least to include Nexus and Haven?  Technically, I know it doesn't make sense, but frankly neither does being able to search all the vendors from inside the quiet bank.  All I know is, I'm dying to buy a Singing Steel Bracer, and if I know one is for sale in Bazaar, I'll trek my butt from Emerald Jungle to get it.  IF I know it's there.  If you think about it, to limit the search to just one zone really is just more code to keep up with in the long run.<br><br><br> <p><div align="center"><b>Uinin Stormsong</b><br>Bard of the Ledenyetz Troupe<br>Herald of Karana<br>~ <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=268592">My Current Playlist</a> ~</div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dalninil>Dalninil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 470<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/27/02 3:35:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1468.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: My patch suggestions (for Bazaar)</span><hr size=1> it'd be neat to screen items by price as well<br><br>ie if i want a 1hs the likely hood of me buying one that would be an upgrade for less than 100 plat is ... well not that likely wadeing though everyones velium and ToFS crap could be avoided with another option 